---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import DocsPagination from '../../../components/DocsPagination.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
  title="CLI Reference — Git Treeline Docs"
  description="Complete CLI reference for Git Treeline. Every command, flag, and subcommand."
  canonical="https://git-treeline.dev/docs/cli/"
  activePage="cli"
>
  <header class="pt-20 sm:pt-24 pb-2 sm:pb-4 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-0">
    <p class="text-sm text-muted mb-4">
      <a href="/docs/" class="text-accent-light hover:text-accent">Docs</a> / CLI
    </p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6 text-balance">CLI reference</h1>
    <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-400 mb-10 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
      Invoked as <code class="text-accent-light">git-treeline</code>, <code class="text-accent-light"
        >git treeline</code
      >, or <code class="text-accent-light">gtl</code>. All three are equivalent.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="docs-guide px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-0 pb-20">
    <h2>Setup</h2>

    <div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-border bg-surface-raised p-4 sm:p-6 mb-8">
      <div class="space-y-0">
        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">install</span>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            One command to get a developer productive. Creates <code class="text-accent-light">.treeline.yml</code> if
            missing, creates user config, installs the post-checkout hook, allocates ports, writes env, and optionally
            enables the local HTTPS router. Safe to re-run — every step is idempotent. Recommended over the
            separate <code class="text-accent-light">init</code> → <code class="text-accent-light">setup</code> flow.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">init</span>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mt-2">
            <span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--project</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--template-db</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--skip-agent-config</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Generate <code class="text-accent-light">.treeline.yml</code> with self-documenting template.
            Auto-detects framework, writes <code class="text-accent-light">AGENTS.md</code> section, detects
            editor.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">new &lt;branch&gt;</span>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mt-2">
            <span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--base</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--path</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--start</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--open</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--force</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--dry-run</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Create worktree + allocate resources + run setup in one step. <code class="text-accent-light"
              >--start</code
            > boots the app after setup. <code class="text-accent-light">--open</code> opens in browser. Works
            without a <code class="text-accent-light">.treeline.yml</code>: detects framework and prompts to init
            for server projects, or creates a plain worktree for non-server projects. Can be run from inside a worktree; prompts for confirmation unless <code class="text-accent-light">--force</code> is passed.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">review &lt;PR#&gt;</span>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mt-2">
            <span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--path</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--start</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--open</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Fetch a GitHub PR into a new worktree with full setup. Requires <code class="text-accent-light"
              >gh</code
            > CLI. From inside a worktree, prompts to switch the current worktree to the PR branch.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">switch &lt;branch-or-PR#&gt;</span>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mt-2">
            <span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--setup</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--restart</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Switch a worktree to a different branch or PR. Fetches, checks out, updates registry, refreshes env. <code
              class="text-accent-light">--setup</code
            > re-runs setup commands. <code class="text-accent-light">--restart</code> bounces the supervised server.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">setup [path]</span>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mt-2">
            <span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--main-repo</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--dry-run</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Full provisioning: allocate ports, copy files, write env, clone DB, run setup commands. Idempotent. When
            reusing an allocation, verifies ports are still free and valid; if not, re-allocates and warns.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">refresh</span>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mt-2">
            <span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--dry-run</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--force</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Re-allocate all worktrees with current config and reservations. Restarts supervised servers automatically.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">release [path]</span>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mt-2">
            <span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--drop-db</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--remove-worktree</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--project</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--all</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--force</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--dry-run</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Free allocated resources. <code class="text-accent-light">--drop-db</code> removes the cloned database. <code
              class="text-accent-light">--remove-worktree</code
            > deletes the directory. <code class="text-accent-light">--all</code> releases everything. Warns on unpushed
            commits.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">prune</span>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mt-2">
            <span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--stale</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--merged</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--drop-db</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--remove-worktree</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--force</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Clean orphaned allocations. <code class="text-accent-light">--stale</code>: worktrees whose directory no
            longer exists. <code class="text-accent-light">--merged</code>: branches merged to <code
              class="text-accent-light">merge_target</code
            >.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">clone &lt;repo&gt;</span>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Clone, detect framework, generate <code class="text-accent-light">.treeline.yml</code> if missing, run
            setup. Does not auto-start.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Server management</h2>

    <div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-border bg-surface-raised p-4 sm:p-6 mb-8">
      <div class="space-y-0">
        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">start</span>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mt-2">
            <span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--with &lt;hooks&gt;</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--await</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--await-timeout</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            <strong class="text-white">Fresh start</strong> (no supervisor): runs <a
              href="/docs/hooks/"
              class="text-accent-light hover:text-accent underline underline-offset-2">start hooks</a
            >, syncs env, refreshes editor, launches supervisor. <strong class="text-white">Resume</strong> (supervisor
            alive): sends start signal. No env sync, no hooks. <code class="text-accent-light">--await</code> blocks
            until TCP accepts on the port. On graceful exit, <code class="text-accent-light">post_stop</code> hooks run
            in reverse.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">stop</span>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mt-2">
            <span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--kill</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Stop the server process. Supervisor stays alive for resume with <code class="text-accent-light">gtl start</code
            >. <code class="text-accent-light">--kill</code> shuts down the supervisor entirely instead of keeping it alive.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">restart</span>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Sync env, push updated vars to supervisor, restart server. Warns if <code class="text-accent-light"
              >commands.start</code
            > differs from what the supervisor is running.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">port</span>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mt-2">
            <span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--json</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Print allocated port for the current worktree. For agents and scripts.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">open</span>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Open in browser: HTTPS branch URL when <code class="text-accent-light">gtl serve</code> is running, else <code
              class="text-accent-light">http://localhost:{'{port}'}</code
            >.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">routes</span>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mt-2">
            <span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--json</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Print the routing URLs for all allocated ports. Shows HTTPS URLs via the router when running, otherwise localhost fallback. Also shows the tunnel URL if configured.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Networking</h2>
    <p class="text-muted mb-4">
      See <a href="/docs/networking/" class="text-accent-light hover:text-accent underline underline-offset-2"
        >Networking guide</a
      > for architecture and design rationale.
    </p>

    <div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-border bg-surface-raised p-4 sm:p-6 mb-8">
      <div class="space-y-0">
        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">serve install</span>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Generate CA, trust it, add port forwarding (443 → router), register background service. Also upgrades an
            existing router. <a
              href="/docs/networking/#the-https-router-gtl-serve"
              class="text-accent-light hover:text-accent underline underline-offset-2">Details</a
            >
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">serve status</span>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Show router state, CA status, port forwarding, and all active routes.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">serve alias &lt;name&gt; [port]</span>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Register a custom hostname on the router. From a worktree directory, port is auto-detected from the allocation. <code class="text-accent-light">--remove &lt;name&gt;</code> to
            unregister. Hot-reloaded within 5 seconds.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">serve uninstall</span>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">Remove service, port forwarding, and CA trust.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">serve hosts sync</span>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Write entries for all active routes to <code class="text-accent-light">/etc/hosts</code>. Required for Safari on macOS with <code class="text-accent-light">localhost</code> domain.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">serve hosts clean</span>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">Remove managed entries from <code class="text-accent-light">/etc/hosts</code>.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">proxy &lt;port&gt; [target]</span>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mt-2">
            <span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--tls</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Bind a well-known port and forward to the current worktree. Target defaults to the first allocated port. <a
              href="/docs/networking/#the-port-proxy-gtl-proxy"
              class="text-accent-light hover:text-accent underline underline-offset-2">Details</a
            >
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">tunnel [port]</span>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mt-2">
            <span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--domain</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--tunnel</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Public HTTPS via Cloudflare. Subcommands: <code class="text-accent-light">tunnel setup</code> for named
            configs, <code class="text-accent-light">tunnel status</code> for connection state, <code
              class="text-accent-light">tunnel default</code
            > to set the active tunnel, <code class="text-accent-light">tunnel remove</code> to delete.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">share [port]</span>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mt-2">
            <span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--tunnel</span
            ><span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--tailscale</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Ephemeral share URL (token-gated Cloudflare or <code class="text-accent-light">--tailscale</code> for
            tailnet-only). Torn down on Ctrl+C.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Cross-worktree</h2>

    <div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-border bg-surface-raised p-4 sm:p-6 mb-8">
      <div class="space-y-0">
        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">resolve &lt;project&gt; [branch]</span>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mt-2">
            <span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--json</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Look up another project's base URL from the registry. Same-branch default; optional explicit branch.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">link &lt;project&gt; &lt;branch&gt;</span>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mt-2">
            <span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
              >--json</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">
            Override <code class="text-accent-light">{'{resolve:project}'}</code> to a fixed branch. Regenerates env and
            restarts server. <code class="text-accent-light">gtl link</code> lists links.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">unlink &lt;project&gt;</span>
          <p class="text-base text-muted mt-2">Remove a link override.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Environment &amp; database</h2>

    <div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-border bg-surface-raised p-4 sm:p-6 mb-8">
      <div class="space-y-0">
        <div class="py-6 sm:py-5 border-b border-surface-border last:border-b-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-white text-base font-semibold">env show</span>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mt-2">
            <span
              class="font-mono text-xs text-yellow-400/80 border border-yellow-400/20 bg-yellow-400/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
